        <span class="sys-label">System 01</span>
        <h3 class="sys-name">The Editorial Operations System</h3>
        <p class="sys-sub">Contributor to Published — Automated End-to-End</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body-text">
      <p>This system solved a specific problem: how do you manage a growing contributor pipeline across outreach, pitching, onboarding, production and payment — with a small team and no room for things to fall through the cracks?</p>
      <p>I architected a multi-board Asana environment connecting every stage of the contributor lifecycle. From the moment a potential contributor is identified, through application, pitch review, onboarding, article production, editorial approval and payment — the system routes, notifies and tracks with minimal manual intervention.</p>
      <p>The design was intentional: human judgment at the decision points that matter (application review, pitch approval, editorial sign-off), automation everywhere else. AI handles the first touchpoint at outreach, pitch screening and generating the content brief, reducing cognitive load while keeping editorial standards high. A learning loop — the Gold Standard Library — continuously refines the AI screener's discernment based on pitches that make it to published drafts.</p>
    </div>

