        <div class="sys-name-row">
          <h3 class="sys-name">The Editorial Intelligence Engine</h3>
          <span class="in-progress-badge">✦ In progress</span>
        </div>
        <p class="sys-sub">AI-Native Content Cycle — From Brief to Published</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Where System 01 layers AI onto existing infrastructure, System 02 is built AI-first from the ground up. It's a bespoke Next.js application designed around a single editorial principle: AI initiates, humans decide and the system learns.</p>
      <p>Content briefs are generated weekly from Claude API calls to a live editorial context document maintained in Supabase. Briefs surface in a clean dashboard for editorial review where they can be approved, rejected or refined. Approved briefs trigger the generation of a first draft — which then goes through inline editorial review, with the system capturing the differential between its version and the final edit. Every piece of editorial feedback becomes a learning signal.</p>
      <p>This learning loop is the architectural centrepiece. The quality threshold is set based on the brief-to-publish rate, and this context gets incorporated into the editorial context document to improve future prompts — ensuring the system genuinely improves from editorial judgment over time.</p>
    </div>

